00:01:35.955 --> 00:01:38.170
Well, the regional assistance
mission in Solomon Islands

00:01:38.170 --> 00:01:42.120
first deployed here
in July of 2003

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:44.890
consisting of some 14 countries.

00:01:44.890 --> 00:01:48.175
They came here because of
troubles between rival gangs

00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:52.940
and ethnic groups that were here
in the Solomon Islands.

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:56.720
And very quickly, they were able
to remove the key threats

00:01:56.720 --> 00:01:58.740
to the people of the Solomon
Islands, a large number of

00:01:58.740 --> 00:02:02.150
weapons and then proceeded to
create their conditions so

00:02:02.150 --> 00:02:04.520
that the Solomon Island's
government could reconstitute

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:08.850
itself and then create a secure
space for it's people.

00:02:11.950 --> 00:02:17.510
Our role here is to deter any
unstabilising forces and

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:19.320
basically give independence
back to the Solomon Island

00:02:19.320 --> 00:02:20.680
government.

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:24.934
We work alongside the PPF, the
Participating Police Forces,

00:02:24.934 --> 00:02:28.140
as well as the Royal Solomon
Islands Police Force.

00:02:32.990 --> 00:02:37.040
I'm a vehicle mechanic working
on Unimog six-wheel drive,

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:40.220
four-wheel drive land rovers.

00:02:40.220 --> 00:02:42.042
And our job with the
guys on the ground

00:02:42.042 --> 00:02:43.430
is extremely important.

00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:46.510
As we say, we've got a fully
petered out six-wheel drive

00:02:46.510 --> 00:02:49.443
vehicle with all their tool
boxes and everything they need

00:02:49.443 --> 00:02:51.370
to do repair.

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:54.340
Infantry, if they have a problem
out in the field with

00:02:54.340 --> 00:02:57.663
their vehicles, we'll go out as
a forward repair team, fix

00:02:57.663 --> 00:03:02.175
it on sight, and then escort
them back or they keep going

00:03:02.175 --> 00:03:03.169
with their duties.

00:03:03.169 --> 00:03:06.540
Combat medical attendant's role
is primarily focused on

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:09.020
providing pre-hospital
care to soldiers.

00:03:09.020 --> 00:03:12.532
Our job is to provide emergency
care to soldiers,

00:03:12.532 --> 00:03:15.281
and we also provide our medical
administration and

00:03:15.281 --> 00:03:16.531
primary health care.

00:03:19.055 --> 00:03:22.730
My role within the army is I'm
a communications systems

00:03:22.730 --> 00:03:28.670
operator, and that entails
robust, secure, and flexible

00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:31.850
communications between the
commander and his troops

00:03:31.850 --> 00:03:33.460
wherever they are
in the field.

00:03:33.460 --> 00:03:36.800
I'm part of the radio
detachment of the

00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:40.170
headquarters, and it's our job
to see that the commanding

00:03:40.170 --> 00:03:44.560
officer has communication with
his troops wherever they be.

00:03:44.560 --> 00:03:46.170
I'm in infantry.

00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:47.920
Infantry soldiers are typically
are known as the

00:03:47.920 --> 00:03:50.130
guys with the rifle on their
shoulder because I'm a hard

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:51.380
readiness reserve member.

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:57.292
I have so far been here in
the Falkland Islands

00:03:57.292 --> 00:03:57.710
definitely the best.

00:03:57.710 --> 00:03:59.270
I'm really proud to
be over here and

00:03:59.270 --> 00:04:00.150
representing my country.

00:04:00.150 --> 00:04:02.840
I feel very honoured to be able
to come over here and

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:05.500
know that what we're doing helps
another country, one of

00:04:05.500 --> 00:04:06.370
our neighbours, the
Solomon Islands.

00:04:06.370 --> 00:04:08.865
It's a really good feeling to
know that we're making a

00:04:08.865 --> 00:04:10.750
difference over here.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:14.450
The highlight for me in the
Solomon Islands has been

00:04:14.450 --> 00:04:16.950
actually doing the job and
seeing it all come together

00:04:16.950 --> 00:04:18.240
and I'm really enjoying it.

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:20.709
And I know there's still
so much more to learn.

00:04:20.709 --> 00:04:22.780
I think that that's actually
knowing that you're doing it

00:04:22.780 --> 00:04:25.350
for real, but not only that, you
can actually look at the

00:04:25.350 --> 00:04:27.360
community and see that what
you're doing is actually

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:28.610
beneficial.

00:04:31.460 --> 00:04:33.350
If we're out in the
jungle, it's hot.

00:04:33.350 --> 00:04:34.820
It's sweaty.

00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:37.280
We're up and down mountains
and it's not easy.

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:41.070
It's not an easy job, and if
you're physically tired, then

00:04:41.070 --> 00:04:42.530
you're going to let
yourself down.

